  "response": "When starting to work out and gain muscle, several supplements can be beneficial:\n\n1. Protein Powder\n- Whey protein is most popular\n- Helps muscle recovery and growth\n- Easy to consume post-workout\n\n2. Creatine Monohydrate\n- Proven to increase muscle mass\n- Improves strength and performance\n- Relatively inexpensive\n- Safe and well-researched\n\n3. Branched-Chain Amino Acids (BCAAs)\n- Helps muscle recovery\n- Reduces muscle soreness\n- Can be taken during workouts\n\n4. Multivitamin\n- Supports overall health\n- Fills nutritional gaps\n- Helps muscle recovery\n\n5. Pre-workout\n- Provides energy\n- Improves focus\n- Enhances performance\n\nImportant considerations:\n- Whole foods should be primary nutrition source\n- Consult with a healthcare professional\n- Quality matters - choose reputable brands\n- Not a substitute for proper diet and exercise\n- Individual results may vary\n\nMost experts recommend starting with whey protein and creatine as foundational supplements for muscle gain.",
